THE MUNCASTER CASTLE. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 5, 1923.) No. 176. Kirlin, Woolsey, Campbell, Hickox & Keating, of New York City (L. De Grove Potter and E. B. Long, Jr., both of White Plains, N. Y., of counsel), for appellant. Austin & Abruzzo, of Brooklyn, N. Y. (Vine H. Smith, of New York City, of’ counsel), for appellee. A. G. Maul, of New York City (G.
